text.tspan: Estimate of the effective reproduction rate (R) of COVID-19, Feb 22,
The reproduction rate represents the average number of new infections caused by a single infected individual. If the rate is
greater than 1, the infection is able to spread in the population. If it is below 1, the number of cases occurring in the
population will gradually decrease to zero.
Data source: Arroyo-Marioli F, Bullano F, Kucinskas S, Rondn-Moreno C (2023)
